  "cacheMaxAge": 30,
  "displayField": "",
  "description": "&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=\"font-size:18px;\"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Description&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=\"color:#000000;\"&gt;This file contains details related to the 2024 actuals.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Division Code&lt;/strong&gt;: &lt;span style=\"color:#000000;\"&gt;A division code is a unique 4-digit code assigned to each division. Generally, division within the same department will share the first two digits of their division code (i.e. 6002 for Police and 6003 for Fire both belong to Public Safety).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Division Name&lt;/strong&gt;: &lt;span style=\"color:#000000;\"&gt;The name of the second level of organization within the City. A Division is part of a Department, which is the highest level of formal organization in the City.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Fund Sub Fund Code&lt;/strong&gt;: &lt;span style=\"color:#000000;\"&gt;Every division belongs to a fund and a sub fund, as specified by a 2-digit code for the fund and a 3-digit code for the sub fund. The majority of the City’s divisions belong to the General Fund specified by fund code 01 and sub fund code 001.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Fund Sub Fund Name&lt;/strong&gt;: &lt;span style=\"color:#000000;\"&gt;The name of the fund sub fund that corresponds to the fund sub fund code. Examples include General Fund, Airport General Operations, Division of Water, Cleveland Public Power, Printing and Reproduction, Division of Mailroom, and Parking Lots General Operations.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Object Code&lt;/strong&gt;: &lt;span style=\"color:#000000;\"&gt;An object code is a unique 4-digit code assigned to each type of expense and/or revenue transaction. Object codes are often reused across multiple unique expenses that fall into the same category.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Object Name&lt;/strong&gt;: &lt;span style=\"color:#000000;\"&gt;The expense and/or revenue transaction that provides more detail about the object code and how the funds are appropriated or spent.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Amount:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=\"color:#000000;\"&gt;The dollars appropriated or spent for a particular object code.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;",
